gness.", "solution_evidence": "Matched Decision Rule 7: 'IF affordability = VERY LOW AND willingness IN [HIGH, MEDIUM, LOW] THEN recommend: Forbearance / Payment Holiday'. This solution directly addresses the customer's stated problem and request from their Jan 27 email.", "problem_description": "", "arrears_clearance_plan": null, "reason_for_willingness": "Insufficient engagement signals to determine willingness. Defaults to VERY LOW per business rules.", "problem_confidence_score": 10, "reason_for_affordability": "Customer is unemployed and stated in their Jan 27 email: 'my current lack of liquidity makes it impossible to meet the standard monthly installments at this moment'. Payment history confirms no successful payments. → VERY LOW", "reason_for_vulnerability": "", "reason_for_ability_to_pay": "Customer is unemployed and stated in their Jan 27 email: 'my current lack of liquidity makes it impossible to meet the standard monthly installments at this moment'. Payment history confirms no successful payments.", "solution_confidence_score": 10, "proposed_email_to_customer": "Subject: Regarding your request for assistance with your Prodigy Finance loan\\nBody: Dear Darshita,\\n\\nThank you for your patience and for proactively reaching out to us. We understand you are facing a difficult period of unemployment, and we want to work with you to find a solution.\\n\\nBased on the information you provided, we would like to offer you a Forbearance plan, which temporarily pauses your payments while you focus on your job search.\\n\\nA specialist will be in touch shortly to discuss the specific terms and finalize the arrangement. We appreciate your commitment to resolving this.\\n\\nBest regards,\\nThe Prodigy Finance Team", "no_of_latest_payments_failed": 0}	pending	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	2026-04-10 19:08:25.016014	88bb298f-0fd9-407b-ad75-1ed7ae2ac794
98	1	1	ed2fbfa1-28fd-4e0f-8e5a-25240eaec5d1	customer_id_4	{"due_date": "2026-04-28", "_payments": [{"amount_paid": "1004", "payment_status": "Received", "date_of_payment": "2026-02-27", "payment_reference": "PAY026", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_4"}, {"amount_paid": "847.75", "payment_status": "Received", "date_of_payment": "2026-01-27", "payment_reference": "PAY010", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_4"}, {"amount_paid": "841.81", "payment_status": "Received", "date_of_payment": "2025-11-24", "payment_reference": "PAY011", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_4"}, {"amount_paid": "2.22", "payment_status": "Received", "date_of_payment": "2025-10-21", "payment_reference": "PAY012", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_4"}, {"amount_paid": "839.78", "payment_status": "Received", "date_of_payment": "2025-10-04", "payment_reference": "PAY013", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_4"}, {"amount_paid": "842", "payment_status": "Received", "date_of_payment": "2025-09-05", "payment_reference": "PAY014", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_4"}, {"amount_paid": "842", "payment_status": "Received", "date_of_payment": "2025-09-05", "payment_reference": "PAY015", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_4"}, {"amount_paid": "842.04", "payment_status": "Received", "date_of_payment": "2025-07-28", "payment_reference": "PAY016", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_4"}, {"amount_paid": "842.08", "payment_status": "Received", "date_of_payment": "2025-05-30", "payment_reference": "PAY017", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_4"}, {"amount_paid": "842.35", "payment_status": "Received", "date_of_payment": "2025-04-01", "payment_reference": "PAY018", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_4"}, {"amount_paid": "842.35", "payment_status": "Received", "date_of_payment": "2025-04-01", "payment_reference": "PAY019", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_4"}, {"amount_paid": "843.04", "payment_status": "Received", "date_of_payment": "2025-02-26", "payment_reference": "PAY020", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_4"}, {"amount_paid": "843.1", "payment_status": "Received", "date_of_payment": "2025-01-24", "payment_reference": "PAY021", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_4"}, {"amount_paid": "843.18", "payment_status": "Received", "date_of_payment": "2024-12-16", "payment_reference": "PAY022", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_4"}, {"amount_paid": "450", "payment_status": "Received", "date_of_payment": "2024-11-21", "payment_reference": "PAY023", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_4"}, {"amount_paid": "450", "payment_status": "Received", "date_of_payment": "2024-10-24", "payment_reference": "PAY024", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_4"}, {"amount_paid": "450", "payment_status": "Received", "date_of_payment": "2024-09-22", "payment_reference": "PAY025", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_4"}, {"amount_paid": "1100", "payment_status": "Received", "date_of_payment": "2026-03-25", "payment_reference": "PAY027", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_4"}], "amount_due": "4910", "dpd_bucket": "90", "minimum_due": "1205", "_conversations": [{"message_content": "Hi Dheeraj\\n \\nI hope you are doing well.\\n \\nMy name is Andisiwe, and I’m your Account Manager here at Prodigy Finance.\\n \\nWe noticed your Prodigy account is now two months in arrears, and we want to help you get back on track. When payments fall behind, there can be serious consequences:\\nYour loan may be reported as in arrears to the Credit Bureau, which can affect your credit score and your ability to access credit in the future.\\nInterest continues to build on missed payments, increasing the overall cost of your loan.\\nIf arrears remain unpaid, your loan could be classified as in default and referred for legal recovery.\\n \\nWe know life doesn’t always go as planned, and catching up on arrears can feel tough. That’swhy we’ve made it simpler to get your loan back on track.\\n\\nHow it works\\n1. Make consistent payments:\\nPay at least three consecutive contractual monthly installments by the payment due\\ndate, either manually or through auto-debit.\\n\\n2. Choose auto-debit (recommended):\\nSet it up in minutes by logging in, adding your bank details, and choosing your preferred\\ndate.\\n\\n3. We’ll reset your schedule:\\nOnce you’ve made three on-time payments, we’ll roll your arrears into your loan balance\\nand spread it across your remaining term so you can move forward with a clean slate.\\n\\n(Your monthly installment may rise slightly, but your loan will stay on track.)\\n\\nWhy auto-debit helps\\n● Hassle-free: Payments happen automatically , no reminders or manual transfers.\\n● On time, every time: Auto-debit means payments land on time, every time.\\n● Stay current: A steady payment history helps keep your loan and credit in good\\nstanding.\\n\\nIf you’re eligible, we recommend setting up auto-debit today—it takes less than two minutes.\\n[Set up auto-debit]\\n\\nIf auto-debit isn’t available for you right now, don’t worry. You can still make your three consecutive contractual payments to your Prodigy Finance account to qualify.\\n\\nIf you have any questions, reply to this email or reach out via your account, we’re here to help.\\n\\nSpeak soon,\\nAndisiwe", "date_and_timestamp": "2/13/2026 13:25", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_4"}, {"message_content": "Hi Dheeraj,\\n \\nThank you for calling in yesterday — it was a pleasure speaking with you.\\n \\nAs discussed during our call, you’re currently unable to repay the full outstanding balance on your loans (including arrears) due to being unemployed. You contacted us to explore the available options and advised that, at this stage, you can afford to make a payment of approximately USD 800.00 toward your loans.\\n \\nBelow is a breakdown of the current outstanding balance for each loan:\\n \\nPDGUS506522\\nPayment due on 28 January 2026: USD 716.01\\nContractual monthly amount: USD 238.90\\nAccumulated arrears: USD 477.11\\nInterest rate: 9.03%\\n \\nPDGUS305344\\nPayment due on 28 January 2026: USD 381.32\\nContractual monthly amount: USD 190.66\\nAccumulated arrears: USD 190.66\\nInterest rate: 9.68%\\n \\nPDGUS326885\\nPayment due on 28 January 2026: USD 835.88\\nContractual monthly amount: USD 417.93\\nAccumulated arrears: USD 417.95\\nInterest rate: 9.52%\\n \\nTo bring your account fully back on schedule this month, a total payment of USD 1,933.21 would be required. However, as you mentioned this is not currently affordable, we recommend making a minimum payment of USD 847.49 by 28 January 2026. This will help prevent your loans from falling further into arrears or moving into a more serious collections stage.\\n \\nAdditionally, our records show that you have already used 6 months of forbearance - to date. However, if your financial circumstances do not improve and you would like to explore further forbearance, please feel free to reach out. We can then share the relevant information and assessment for you to complete. Please note that, if approved, an additional 3 months of forbearance would be the final forbearance available for the remaining term of your loan.\\n \\nIf you have any questions or would like to discuss the next steps, please don’t hesitate to contact us.\\n \\nKind regards,\\nLynn", "date_and_timestamp": "1/13/2026 11:13", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_4"}, {"message_content": "Hi Dheeraj\\n \\nI hope you're doing well.\\n \\nMy name is Michael, and I’m your Account Manager here at Prodigy Finance. I recently tried calling you on +1 (214) 471-8605 - are you still using this number?  If not, please update your contact details in the Prodigy Finance app or share your preferred number with me.\\n \\nWe want to work with you to get things back on track as soon as possible.\\n \\nWhen payments fall behind, there can be serious consequences:\\nYour loan may be reported as in arrears to the Credit Bureau, which can affect your credit score and your ability to access credit in the future.\\nInterest continues to build on missed payments, increasing the overall cost of your loan.\\nIf arrears remain unpaid, your loan could be classified as in default and referred for legal recovery.\\n \\nTo avoid this, we kindly ask that you make a payment of USD 476.85, USD 377.61, and USD 827.97 by 28 November 2025. This includes both your missed instalment and the current month's due amount.\\n \\nIf you’re paying from a US, UK, or EU account, setting up auto-debit via the Prodigy Finance app is the simplest way to avoid missing future payments. You can check our FAQs to get started.\\n \\nIf you have any questions or need help making your payment, please don’t hesitate to reach out. You can also schedule a call with the team. We’d be happy to assist.\\n \\nLooking forward to hearing from you.\\n \\nSpeak soon\\nMichael", "date_and_timestamp": "11/19/2025 14:05", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_4"}], "_payment_count": 18, "_conversation_count": 3, "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_4"}	\N		9	Customer explicitly stated they are 'unemployed' in the conversation log from 2026-01-13. Payment history confirms that recent payments ($1004, $1100) are below the minimum due of $1205.	Encourage the customer to increase their next payment to meet or exceed the minimum amount due of $1205. Acknowledge their positive payment behavior and frame meeting the minimum as the next key step to stop arrears growth and get back on track.	9	The customer has MEDIUM Affordability and HIGH Willingness. Per Decision Rule #3, the correct action is to encourage payment at or above the minimum due with a supportive tone. This solution directly implements the client's policy.		1004	This figure is the median of the three successful payments made in the last three months ($847.75, $1004, $1100). This is a reliable indicator of recent, demonstrated capacity.	0	Subject: Great progress on your Prodigy Finance account\n\nBody: Hi Dheeraj,\n\nThank you for your recent consistent payments, including your latest payment of $1100. We really appreciate your commitment to getting your account back on track.\n\nThe next important milestone is to cover the minimum amount due of $1205. Paying this amount will stop your arrears from growing further and is a key step toward restoring your account to good standing.\n\nWe see you are making great progress, and we're here to support you. Please let us know if you have any questions.\n\nKind regards,\nThe Prodigy Finance Team	{"willingness": "HIGH", "combined_cmd": null, "conversation": "In a Jan 2026 call, the customer stated they were unemployed but could afford ~$800/month. They have since made three consecutive payments, each exceeding this stated capacity. No response to a Feb 2026 re-aging offer is recorded.", "affordability": "MEDIUM", "customer_guid": "customer_id_4", "vulnerability": false, "ability_to_pay": 1004, "internal_action": "", "payment_history": "Customer made three successful payments in the last 3 months: $1100 on Mar 25, $1004 on Feb 27, and $847.75 on Jan 27. Payments are consistent and increasing but remain below the minimum due.", "problem_evidence": "Customer explicitly stated they are 'unemployed' in the conversation log from 2026-01-13. Payment history confirms that recent payments ($1004, $1100) are below the minimum due of $1205.", "proposed_solution": "Encourage the customer to increase their next payment to meet or exceed the minimum amount due of $1205. Acknowledge their positive payment behavior and frame meeting the minimum as the next key step to stop arrears growth and get back on track.", "solution_evidence": "The customer has MEDIUM Affordability and HIGH Willingness. Per Decision Rule #3, the correct action is to encourage payment at or above the minimum due with a supportive tone. This solution directly implements the client's policy.", "problem_description": "", "arrears_clearance_plan": null, "reason_for_willingness": "In a Jan 2026 call, the customer stated they were unemployed but could afford ~$800/month. They have since made three consecutive payments, each exceeding this stated capacity. No response to a Feb 2026 re-aging offer is recorded. → HIGH", "problem_confidence_score": 9, "reason_for_affordability": "This figure is the median of the three successful payments made in the last three months ($847.75, $1004, $1100). This is a reliable indicator of recent, demonstrated capacity. → MEDIUM", "reason_for_vulnerability": "", "reason_for_ability_to_pay": "This figure is the median of the three successful payments made in the last three months ($847.75, $1004, $1100). This is a reliable indicator of recent, demonstrated capacity.", "solution_confidence_score": 9, "proposed_email_to_customer": "Subject: Great progress on your Prodigy Finance account\\n\\nBody: Hi Dheeraj,\\n\\nThank you for your recent consistent payments, including your latest payment of $1100. We really appreciate your commitment to getting your account back on track.\\n\\nThe next important milestone is to cover the minimum amount due of $1205. Paying this amount will stop your arrears from growing further and is a key step toward restoring your account to good standing.\\n\\nWe see you are making great progress, and we're here to support you. Please let us know if you have any questions.\\n\\nKind regards,\\nThe Prodigy Finance Team", "no_of_latest_payments_failed": 0}	pending	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	2026-04-10 19:09:05.835773	88bb298f-0fd9-407b-ad75-1ed7ae2ac794
