8	3	ed2fbfa1-28fd-4e0f-8e5a-25240eaec5d1	test data-Beacon Demo - Conversation data.csv	CSV	26726	15	15	0	conversation_history	[{"_status": "created", "_message": "Created successfully", "message_content": "Hi Darshitaben,\\n \\nThank you for completing the assessment.\\n \\nOur specialist team has kindly requested the most recent three months bank statements.\\n \\nKindly ensure that the requested information is submitted to us before 28 February 2026. You may reply directly to this email.\\n \\nTake care,\\nMpho", "date_and_timestamp": "2/26/2026 13:49", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_3"}, {"_status": "created", "_message": "Created successfully", "message_content": "Thank you for your response, I will get back to you shortly.\\n\\nRegards,\\nTolulope O. Omotayo\\n", "date_and_timestamp": "3/5/2026 17:28", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_2"}, {"_status": "created", "_message": "Created successfully", "message_content": "Hi Tolulope,\\n \\nFrom point 1-4, I provided a full transactional statement to confirm the relevant information.\\n \\n5. A settlement offer was provided to confirm the settlement amount which is valid till 30 March 2026.\\n \\n6. The current status is delinquent.\\n \\n7. The account is still maintained by Prodigy Finance.\\n \\nWe hope this gives you the clarity you need.\\n \\nIf you need further assistance, please let us know and we’ll be happy to help!\\n \\nKind regards,\\nThaakirah", "date_and_timestamp": "3/5/2026 17:28", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_2"}, {"_status": "created", "_message": "Created successfully", "message_content": "However, my requests are detailed in the letter sent to you.\\nThey are here listed below. The letter is also attached again.\\n \\n\\n1. The original principal amount disbursed to Boston University in December 2021. \\n\\n2. A detailed breakdown of all interest accrued to date, including any capitalized interest. \\n\\n3. A breakdown of any late fees, penalties, or additional charges applied to the account. \\n\\n4. A transaction history showing how my $6,000 payment made in December 2023 was applied (whether to principal, interest, or fees). \\n\\n5. The current total payoff amount as of the date of your response. \\n\\n6. Confirmation of the present status of the account. In that regard, I would like to know the status is current, delinquent, defaulted, charged off, or otherwise. \\n\\n7. Confirmation as to whether the account remains with Prodigy Finance or has been assigned or transferred to any third party. If transferred, please provide the details. \\n\\n\\n\\nHoping to hear from you soon.\\nThank you for your understanding.\\n\\nRegards,\\nTolulope O. Omotayo", "date_and_timestamp": "3/5/2026 15:24", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_2"}, {"_status": "created", "_message": "Created successfully", "message_content": "Good afternoon Andisiwe.\\nI sent an email to Prodigy last Monday and i'm yet to receive a response.\\nMy request is for a payoff statement with some details requested. I am not asking for a settlement offer at this moment as responded to by your AI agent.\\nKindly have a look into the email and let me have the requested information as detailed in my email - Subject: Loan ID PDGUS271931 – Request for Payoff Statement.\\nHoping to hear from you soon.\\nHave a blessed day.\\n\\n\\nRegards,\\nTolulope O. Omotayo", "date_and_timestamp": "3/4/2026 13:21", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_2"}, {"_status": "created", "_message": "Created successfully", "message_content": "Hi  Sathwik\\n\\nI hope you are doing well.\\n \\nWe recently shared an assessment survey with you, and I wanted to follow up as we haven’t received your completed form yet. Completing this survey helps us understand your current circumstances so that we can provide the right support.\\n \\nTo ensure your request for forbearance is reviewed in time, please complete this assessment in its entirety and provide all the requested supporting documentation to be considered for forbearance at your earliest convenience.\\n \\nMaking payment promptly will help you avoid:\\nYour loan being reported as in arrears to the Credit Bureau, which could affect your credit score and future access to credit.\\nAdditional interest accruing, which increases the overall cost of your loan.\\nYour loan being referred for legal action, which may involve additional costs.\\nReceiving CCA notices, which we are required to send as a regulated lender under the FCA.\\n \\nLooking forward to your reply.\\n \\nSpeak soon,\\nAndisiwe", "date_and_timestamp": "3/10/2026 8:00", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_1"}, {"_status": "updated", "_message": "Updated successfully", "message_content": "Hi Sathwik,\\n\\nThank you for letting us know about your financial situation. We understand this may be a stressful time, and we want you to feel supported and fully informed about the options available to you.\\n\\nProdigy is committed to supporting customers in financial hardship, and we want to ensure that you are well informed about the options available and any impact on you. If you are considering requesting forbearance,  please read the information below carefully before submitting your request.\\n\\nWhat is forbearance?\\n\\nIf you want to find out more about Forbearance.\\n\\nIt is important to note that we generally only approve arrangements of up to 6 months within any 12-month timeframe, granted in two 3 month periods and subject to the overall maximum forbearance of 9 months over the entire duration of the loan(s). Each forbearance request is assessed by our specialist team who may request supporting documents to verify the information provided to support the request. Although forbearance can provide temporary relief by allowing you to reduce or pause your payments for a specified period, it is crucial to understand that forbearance should be considered as a last resort. It is always beneficial to explore other options first, before resorting to forbearance.\\n\\nWhat happens during forbearance?\\n\\nIf your loan(s) is placed in an arrangement, the loan agreement terms won’t change. This means that:\\n\\nInterest will still accrue on the outstanding balance while your loan is in an arrangement. This can increase the overall cost of credit, and you may end up paying more in the long run.\\n\\nIf you have already missed payments and are in arrears before requesting forbearance, the arrears will remain on your account. Interest will accrue on the arrears which could increase the overall cost of credit.\\n\\nIf you are in a reduced payment arrangement, you will be expected to pay the full reduced payment each month that the loan(s) is in the arrangement. Any missed payment will accrue as arrears, resulting in your loan status worsening and could lead to default.\\n\\nWhen you return to making full payments, your monthly payment will be slightly higher than usual. This ensures that you are still able to pay off the entire loan balance on schedule.\\n\\nHow might this impact my credit score?\\n\\nProdigy is required to report according to the rules of the relevant credit bureaus in your country of residence. We will report your loan(s) as in forbearance during the arrangement period. This may be visible to other creditors for an extended period after your arrangement comes to an end, and could affect your credit score or limit your ability to obtain new loans or access other credit lines in the future. When you resume your regular repayments on your loan(s), we will report this to the relevant credit bureau, which may improve your credit score over time.\\n\\nIf you have already missed payments and are in arrears before requesting forbearance, the arrears will remain on your credit report and be visible to other credit providers.\\n\\nYou can visit our FAQs for more information on how our forbearance option works.\\n\\nRemember, it is always in your best interest to continue making regular, on-time payments towards your loan(s).  Forbearance is a temporary measure that is limited in its availability and duration.\\n\\nIf you can make payments towards your loan, you should continue to do so to maintain financial stability.\\n\\nIf you would like to proceed with your forbearance request, please complete the assessment below to tell us more about your financial circumstances.\\n\\nBy clicking on the link below, you are consenting to our use of the information provided to assess your current affordability in applying for any one of our available arrangement packages. The information provided will remain confidential and is only intended to help us understand your current situation.\\n\\nPlease complete this assessment in its entirety and provide all the requested supporting documentation to be considered for forbearance. This assessment link is custom to your account specifically and should not be shared with others.\\n\\nWe will provide you with feedback within 10 business days from the date that your completed assessment is received.\\n\\nYou must complete all parts of the assessment and submit it to us with all the required supporting documentation for your application to be considered.\\n\\nImportant:\\n\\nIf you select “I recently lost my job” in the assessment, please reply to this email with a copy of your termination letter or separation agreement from your employer.\\n\\nIf you select “I am doing an unpaid internship,” “unpaid employment,” or “voluntary employment,” please reply to this email with a copy of the letter confirming your unpaid internship or voluntary role from your employer or organization.\\n\\nYour application will not be considered complete until we receive these supporting documents by email.\\n\\nImpact of forbearance on auto-debit payments\\n\\nIf you have an auto-debit set up for your payments, you need to ensure that we receive your completed assessment at least ten (10) days before your auto-debit date. This is to ensure that your auto debit settings are adjusted in time to prevent payments from being processed if the request is approved. If we do not receive your request in time, your payment will be debited from your account as normal on the selected date.\\n\\nDue date for submission of forbearance request\\n\\nPlease note that you have 10 days from today to complete and submit your forbearance assessment. If we receive your arrangement request after the 28th of this month and it is approved, your arrangement will only begin from NEXT CYCLE MONTH. This means your regular payment for THIS CYCLE MONTH will still be due as scheduled.\\n\\nIf there’s anything you’d like us to explain further, don’t hesitate to let us know. We’re here to help.\\n\\nSpeak soon,\\nVirtual AI Assistant, Lily", "date_and_timestamp": "2/20/2026 10:38", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_1"}, {"_status": "updated", "_message": "Updated successfully", "message_content": "Hi Sathwik,\\n\\nThank you for letting us know about your financial situation. We understand this may be a stressful time, and we want you to feel supported and fully informed about the options available to you.\\n\\nProdigy is committed to supporting customers in financial hardship, and we want to ensure that you are well informed about the options available and any impact on you. If you are considering requesting forbearance,  please read the information below carefully before submitting your request.\\n\\nWhat is forbearance?\\n\\nIf you want to find out more about Forbearance.\\n\\nIt is important to note that we generally only approve arrangements of up to 6 months within any 12-month timeframe, granted in two 3 month periods and subject to the overall maximum forbearance of 9 months over the entire duration of the loan(s). Each forbearance request is assessed by our specialist team who may request supporting documents to verify the information provided to support the request. Although forbearance can provide temporary relief by allowing you to reduce or pause your payments for a specified period, it is crucial to understand that forbearance should be considered as a last resort. It is always beneficial to explore other options first, before resorting to forbearance.\\n\\nWhat happens during forbearance?\\n\\nIf your loan(s) is placed in an arrangement, the loan agreement terms won’t change. This means that:\\n\\nInterest will still accrue on the outstanding balance while your loan is in an arrangement. This can increase the overall cost of credit, and you may end up paying more in the long run.\\n\\nIf you have already missed payments and are in arrears before requesting forbearance, the arrears will remain on your account. Interest will accrue on the arrears which could increase the overall cost of credit.\\n\\nIf you are in a reduced payment arrangement, you will be expected to pay the full reduced payment each month that the loan(s) is in the arrangement. Any missed payment will accrue as arrears, resulting in your loan status worsening and could lead to default.\\n\\nWhen you return to making full payments, your monthly payment will be slightly higher than usual. This ensures that you are still able to pay off the entire loan balance on schedule.\\n\\nHow might this impact my credit score?\\n\\nProdigy is required to report according to the rules of the relevant credit bureaus in your country of residence. We will report your loan(s) as in forbearance during the arrangement period. This may be visible to other creditors for an extended period after your arrangement comes to an end, and could affect your credit score or limit your ability to obtain new loans or access other credit lines in the future. When you resume your regular repayments on your loan(s), we will report this to the relevant credit bureau, which may improve your credit score over time.\\n\\nIf you have already missed payments and are in arrears before requesting forbearance, the arrears will remain on your credit report and be visible to other credit providers.\\n\\nYou can visit our FAQs for more information on how our forbearance option works.\\n\\nRemember, it is always in your best interest to continue making regular, on-time payments towards your loan(s).  Forbearance is a temporary measure that is limited in its availability and duration.\\n\\nIf you can make payments towards your loan, you should continue to do so to maintain financial stability.\\n\\nIf you would like to proceed with your forbearance request, please complete the assessment below to tell us more about your financial circumstances.\\n\\nBy clicking on the link below, you are consenting to our use of the information provided to assess your current affordability in applying for any one of our available arrangement packages. The information provided will remain confidential and is only intended to help us understand your current situation.\\n\\nPlease complete this assessment in its entirety and provide all the requested supporting documentation to be considered for forbearance. This assessment link is custom to your account specifically and should not be shared with others.\\n\\nWe will provide you with feedback within 10 business days from the date that your completed assessment is received.\\n\\nYou must complete all parts of the assessment and submit it to us with all the required supporting documentation for your application to be considered.\\n\\nImportant:\\n\\nIf you select “I recently lost my job” in the assessment, please reply to this email with a copy of your termination letter or separation agreement from your employer.\\n\\nIf you select “I am doing an unpaid internship,” “unpaid employment,” or “voluntary employment,” please reply to this email with a copy of the letter confirming your unpaid internship or voluntary role from your employer or organization.\\n\\nYour application will not be considered complete until we receive these supporting documents by email.\\n\\nImpact of forbearance on auto-debit payments\\n\\nIf you have an auto-debit set up for your payments, you need to ensure that we receive your completed assessment at least ten (10) days before your auto-debit date. This is to ensure that your auto debit settings are adjusted in time to prevent payments from being processed if the request is approved. If we do not receive your request in time, your payment will be debited from your account as normal on the selected date.\\n\\nDue date for submission of forbearance request\\n\\nPlease note that you have 10 days from today to complete and submit your forbearance assessment. If we receive your arrangement request after the 28th of this month and it is approved, your arrangement will only begin from NEXT CYCLE MONTH. This means your regular payment for THIS CYCLE MONTH will still be due as scheduled.\\n\\nIf there’s anything you’d like us to explain further, don’t hesitate to let us know. We’re here to help.\\n\\nSpeak soon,\\nVirtual AI Assistant, Lily", "date_and_timestamp": "1/8/2026 14:44", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_1"}, {"_status": "updated", "_message": "Updated successfully", "message_content": "Hi \\n\\nThis is Sathwik Ram Yeldhandi , my loan number \\nPDGUS618851 I need an extension to pay the amount about a month, since I m facing some financial issues I cannot pay the amount this month I will start paying the amount next month for sure. \\n\\nThank you ", "date_and_timestamp": "12/11/2025 14:30", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_1"}, {"_status": "updated", "_message": "Updated successfully", "message_content": "Dear Prodigy Finance Collections/Payments Team,\\n\\nI am writing to formally address the overdue status of my account (Loan ID: PDGUS493193 & PDGUS551765). I am currently 90 days past due on my installments, and I am reaching out to resolve this situation before the account moves toward default proactively.\\n\\nI am currently experiencing severe financial hardship due to involuntary unemployment following the completion of my studies. Despite an intensive job search, I have not yet secured a stable income. As an international graduate, I am committed to fulfilling my debt obligations, but my current lack of liquidity makes it impossible to meet the standard monthly installments at this moment.\\n\\nI value my relationship with Prodigy Finance and wish to keep my account in good standing. I would like to request the following formally:\\n\\n1.\\nA temporary suspension of payments for the next few months to allow me to finalize my employment search.\\n2.\\nI request a restructuring of my loan terms. This could include extending the total loan tenure to reduce monthly installments or moving to \\"interest-only\\" payments for a set period.\\n\\nI am eager to cooperate with your team. I can provide documentation of my job applications or a summary of my current financial status upon request. My goal is to establish a sustainable payment plan that reflects my current reality while ensuring the loan is eventually repaid in full.\\n\\nPlease let me know which documents are required to formalize this hardship application. I am also available for a phone call at*+1-765-532-5183* to discuss this further.\\n\\nThank you for your understanding and for helping me find a path forward during this difficult transition.\\n\\nPS: I sent a formal hardship and restructuring request for Loans PDGUS493193 and PDGUS551765 on January 15th. Can you please confirm it has been received and assigned to a case manager?\\n\\nBest regards\\n\\nDarshita Patel", "date_and_timestamp": "1/27/2026 16:30", "customer / account / loan id": "customer_id_3"}, {"_status": "updated", "_message": "Updated successfully", "message_content": "Dear Prodigy Finance Collections/Payments Team,\\n\\nI am writing to formally address the overdue status of my account (Loan ID: PDGUS493193 & PDGUS551765). I am currently 90 days past due on my installments, and I am reaching out to resolve this situa